\bar{R}^{ej}_{\\alpha } = \\bar{R}^{e}(\\tau _{\\alpha }^{j})$. We therefore have Step 1. Effect ofc$c$andτdmmax$\\tau ^{\\rm max}_{dm}$onΔRαdm$\\Delta R_{\\alpha }^{dm}$. Equation (A37) implies that the derivative ofταdm$\\tau _{\\alpha }^{dm}$with respect toτ∗$\\tau ^*$is To assess the effect ofτdmmax$\\tau ^{\\rm max}_{dm}$onΔRαdm$\\Delta R_{\\alpha }^{dm}$, note thatΦ(τ)=Ψ(τ)/Ψ(ταdm)$\\Phi (\\tau)= \\Psi (\\tau)/\\Psi (\\tau _{\\alpha }^{dm})$, and thus, for somea∈[0,1]$a \\in [0,1]$,Φ−1(a)=Ψ−1(Ψ(ταdm)a)$\\Phi ^{-1}(a)= \\Psi ^{-1}(\\Psi (\\tau _{\\alpha }^{dm})a)$. According to Equation (A37), one then obtains Moreover, under Assumption1, densityψ$\\psi$has a finite first-order moment even whenτdmmax$\\tau ^{\\rm max}_{dm}$goes to infinity. Consequently,τψ(τ)$\\tau \\psi (\\tau)$goes to zero whenτ$\\tau$goes to∞$\\infty$. So, forτdmmax$\\tau ^{\\rm max}_{dm}$large enoughτdmmaxψ(τdmmax)<τ∗ψ(τ∗)$\\tau ^{\\rm max}_{dm}\\psi (\\tau ^{\\rm max}_{dm}) < \\tau ^*\nSupporting Information: Appendix S1: Internet Appendix. Replication Code. Please note: The publisher is not responsible for the content or functionality of any supporting information supplied by the authors. Any queries (other than missing content) should be directed to the corresponding author for the article.\nREFERENCES: \n\n\n你需要做出全面、简单、直接的总结。总结字数不超过250字。分析给你的学术论文，用一句话进行总结，回答以下问题：该论文研究的是什么领域，它想要解决什么问题，之前是如何解决的，作者是如何解决的，并重点关注作者提出的方法。 \n\n[Warning] 最后，我想给你一些撰写学术博客的提示作为参考：  \n1. 使用第三人称和对话语气，要有趣并吸引读者的兴趣。\n2. 简化复杂概念：保持简单明了。 字数限制为250字。\n3. 请注意，这篇文章不是你写的。\n"}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '**Title:** "Equilibrium Data Mining and Data Abundance"  \n\n**Summary:**  \nThis finance theory paper investigates how the "big data revolution"—specifically the explosion of new datasets ("data abundance") and lower computing costs—impacts asset managers’ strategies, market efficiency, and fund performance. Prior work conflated these two forces, but the authors disentangle their effects using a novel equilibrium model where "quant" funds (data miners) search for predictive signals through iterative exploration, while traditional "expert" funds rely on fixed skills. Key findings reveal that while data abundance *initially* boosts quant fund growth and price informativeness, it paradoxically reduces their search intensity and capital allocation over time as markets become too efficient. Meanwhile, lower processing costs unambiguously favor quants. The model challenges assumptions that data proliferation uniformly benefits quantitative strategies, highlighting a self-limiting dynamic where excessive data erodes profit opportunities. By formalizing how data abundance reshapes competition between human judgment and algorithmic trading, the paper offers fresh insights into the rise—and potential plateau—of quant finance.'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '\n根据你提供的总结，为这篇论文的分析想出一个通用的标题。这个标题需要涵盖文章中最具创新性的元素，并吸引读者的注意力。创建一个引人注目的标题，这个标题需要像新闻标题一样引人注目，而不是文章标题的重述。限制在25个字以内。\n格式限制：\n1. 只需给出你写的标题，不需要其他废话\n2. **{你的给定标题}**\n'}], 'model': 'deepseek-reasoner', 'stream': False}}
