here "quant" funds (data miners) search for predictive signals through iterative exploration, while traditional "expert" funds rely on fixed skills. Key findings reveal that while data abundance *initially* boosts quant fund growth and price informativeness, it paradoxically reduces their search intensity and capital allocation over time as markets become too efficient. Meanwhile, lower processing costs unambiguously favor quants. The model challenges assumptions that data proliferation uniformly benefits quantitative strategies, highlighting a self-limiting dynamic where excessive data erodes profit opportunities. By formalizing how data abundance reshapes competition between human judgment and algorithmic trading, the paper offers fresh insights into the rise—and potential plateau—of quant finance.'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '\n根据你提供的总结，为这篇论文的分析想出一个通用的标题。这个标题需要涵盖文章中最具创新性的元素，并吸引读者的注意力。创建一个引人注目的标题，这个标题需要像新闻标题一样引人注目，而不是文章标题的重述。限制在25个字以内。\n格式限制：\n1. 只需给出你写的标题，不需要其他废话\n2. **{你的给定标题}**\n'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '**{数据洪流：量化基金的繁荣悖论}**'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '提取关键词，关键词要实用，并且要更关注文章的内容。无需解释。提出学术文章中更常见的关键词\n\n示例：\n"AI关键词": [\n        "异常交易信号",\n        "信息发布日期",\n        "资产定价",\n        "Compustat快照",\n        "投资组合再平衡",\n        "信息衰减",\n        "市场效率"\n    ]\n '}], 'model': 'deepseek-reasoner', 'stream': False}}
